6:
I want it! I want it so bad, ugh! What
to do...
10:
If I buy it and get found out, I'll just
be ridiculed in front of everyone
again...
21:
Wh-what on earth are you doing in
a place like this?!
26:
We're just passin' through on our
way to get some grub.
34:
Nothing! Absolutely nothing! I wasn't
looking at anything!
37:
This young one has been staring at
my wares for quite some time now,
all but salivating!
42:
Isn't it illegal to give out information
on customers like that or
something?!
55:
So what? It's not like I want it or
anything!
61: I would like to have it.
67: We should buy a matching pair.
78:
No, it's not that... it just wouldn't look
good on me!
82:
That's not true. Someone once told
me that thinking like that was a
waste.
103:
Wh-why did you... I can't believe you
bought these...
113:
Hey, Karyl, how about joining us for
dinner tonight? We haven't picked a
place yet, though.
116:
I mean, if you insist, I guess I could
go...
120:
Actually... I just thought of a good
restaurant we can go to!
127:
I didn't know this was here—I must
have passed this place by without
realizing it.
131:
Food is food—it doesn't matter
where it comes from. Let's get to
eatin'!
148:
This is just incredible! The flavor is
perfect, and they really nailed the
seasoning—all for this price?!
153:
I had no idea an eatery like this
existed in Palpebra. You did well to
find it.
157:
I've gotten very familiar with the
local restaurants—mostly because
Pecorine and the others drag me
around the city on their little food
tours!
160:
Though we really should be tending
to more important matters than
that...
165:
She says that, but really she's glad
to be chowin' down on this
awesome meal.
185:
It's important to afford yourself
some room to breathe—especially
in the middle of a grand,
unpredictable adventure!
192:
But I can't afford to slip up. I have a
duty to fulfill.
193:
And to do so I desperately need that
magic spell... but it just won't work!
202:
You aren't worthless, Karyl. Magic or
no magic.
207:
I'm no expert, but it sounds to me
like you're pouncin' to conclusions.
It's not like you'll never be able to
use this magic again.
212:
You can still try travelling to different
worlds and testing out your spells
there.
217:
You're certainly optimistic—or
maybe I should say naive. I'm
worried I'll let my guard down if I'm
around you for too long...
220:
Maybe I already have... I've told you
things that I probably shouldn't have.
221:
Would you believe I haven't shared
these worries with any of the others?
226:
Your friends at the Gourmet Guild?
You must really care for them, Karyl.
231:
Huh? What do you mean "care for
them"?!
237:
Well, I figure it's easier for you to
open up to us since we're not as
close.
242:
Indeed. Some things cannot be said
precisely because you treasure the
other party so dearly.
246:
No, that's not why I haven't told
them... I have other much more
personal circumstances.
249:
Interesting that you didn't deny
caring for them.
257:
What a great meal. My plate's not
even empty, and I'm already full!
262:
Shut up with the sentimental crap! If
you keep saying stuff like that, I'm
going to bury you in the ground!
